text:
Measurable deficiencies, such as the lack of a proper drainage system or an inadequate number of parking spaces, can be corrected by filing for a variance. The Board of Zoning Appeals (BZA) is responsible for granting variances to property owners who are unable to comply with certain zoning regulations.
The BZA meets on the second and fourth Monday of each month at 7:00 p.m., in Council Chambers located on the first floor of City Hall, 1 Courthouse Square. Applications must be filed no later than noon two weeks prior to the meeting date. For more information about applying for a variance please contact Planning & Development Services Department at 419-213-4345.
A variance may only be granted if all four conditions below have been met:
(1) That there are special circumstances applicable to the property involved that do not apply generally to other properties in the same district;
(2) That literal enforcement of the provisions would result in unnecessary hardship upon the applicant; provided however, that this shall not include any hardships caused by changes in economic trends or market values occurring after the adoption of the ordinance under which the application was made;
(3) That the authorization of the variance will not cause substantial detriment to adjacent neighbors or otherwise impair the purpose and intent
